Function.Definition:
Creates a new table.

      o 1st argument is a list of column names
      o 2nd argument is a list of types for each column
      o any further arguments are rows to be added to the table
      o A table with the given rows is returned. No rows are required.

      Example:
      columns = {"make", "MSRP", "HP", "cylinders"};
      coltypes = {"varchar", "int64", "integer","int64"};
      row1 = {"dodge", 20000, 250, 4};
      row2 = {"ford", 30000, 200, 6};
      table = newtable( "cars", columns, coltypes, row1, row2,...};

The name of the table can be specified as the first argument, but is not required. The default name is "nodeList".
